en_789601_0	The National “Aluth Sahal Mangalya” was presided over by President Maithripala Sirisena at the premises of the Jaya Sri Maha Bodhiya in Anuradhapura on Saturday.
en_789601_1	Speaking at the event, the President stated that the government will introduce a framework to financially strengthen the agrarian community.
en_789601_2	The first portion of rice from the harvest reaped from the Maha Season was offered to the Jaya Sri Mahabodhi and the ceremony was organised by the Venerable Pallegama Srinivasa Thero.
en_789601_3	The traditional ceremony is aimed at blessing the country and the nation as well as making the country self-sufficient in rice.
en_789601_4	The leader of the indigenous community and his tribe were also present during this ceremony.
en_789601_5	During the event the President presented a bowl of organically grown rice,  free of pesticides, to the Maha Sangha.
en_789601_6	The President also distributed seed paddy for the cultivation of this form of rice in  the nine provinces.
